summary: 03/25/1993: An unknown group attacked a military compound in Lome, housing the President of Togo, Gnassingbe Eyadema, killing five and injuring one. President Eyadema was not killed in this attack.
addnotes: The Togo government accused neighboring Ghana of supporting the attackers.
scite1: "Togo minister accuses Ghana over attack on Eyadema residence,” Agence France Presse, March 29, 1993.
scite2: Combiete Combey, “Gunmen Attack President's Home in Togo, Kill Top Aide,” The Associated Press, March 25, 1993.
scite3: "Attack On Presidential Barracks Repulsed, Eyadema Safe,” The Associated Press, March 25, 1993.
